name: pinto bean production | pinto bean | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/25309/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 tonne of dried pinto bean (<15% moisture) during May-August, 2020, at 1057.44 ha pinto bean farms located in the Province of Alberta, Canada. Yield values were averaged over 2018-2020, and farms have an average yield of 3296.28 kg grain (<15% moisture) per ha for these crop cycles. The system boundaries include the production of all crop inputs (e.g. seeds, fertilizers, crop protection products, and fuel) and consider nitrogen credits derived from biological N fixation associated with dried pinto bean production. Irrigation is included. The sowing date for the crop is May 2020 and the harvesting date is August 2020. The seeding rate is 24.08 kg/tonne of pinto bean production. Fertilizer applied contain nitrogen (as N) 17.02 kg/tonne, phosphate (as P2O5) 5.63 kg/tonne, potash (as K2O) 3.17 kg/tonne, and sulfur (as S) 3.14 kg/tonne. Predominant crop protection applied contain active ingredients of glyphosate 0.075 kg/tonne, bentazon 0.363 kg/tonne, and boscalid 0.055 kg/tonne. Machinery is used for tillage, fertilizer application, pre-plant herbicide application, planting, rolling, post-emergent herbicide application, inter-row cultivating/scuffing/hilling, fungicide application, pre-harvest desiccation, pull/undercut/knife, windrow/swathing, harvesting, and other with total fuel consumption of 17.39 kg/tonne.

Starting inputs for this activity include seed, fertilizer, crop protection products and fuel on the farm. This activity begins with soil preparation about 39 weeks after the harvest of the previous crop. The soil is prepared for cultivation in last week of May and the sowing of seeds started about 5 days after soil preparation.

This activity ends with navy bean drying to <15% moisture at farm gate. This takes place in September, 17 weeks after the activity starts. The activity includes the infrastructures and use of agricultural machinery.

Physical (mass) allocation; N credits from biological N fixation are included as a system expansion, consistent with the ISO 14044 multifunctionality hierarchy. A negative input was included of ammonia N fertilizer to represent amount of N fixed.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/011:Growing of non-perennial crops/0111:Growing of cereals (except rice), leguminous crops and oil seeds

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Soil cultivating date for the main crop: May 2020; Harvesting date for the main crop: September 2020. Total time from the date of sowing to the date of harvesting comes to 17 weeks. Yield data were collected and averaged for three crop cycles (2018-2020). All other data were collected for 2020 only.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Refers to weighted-average production in the Province of Alberta, Canada
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Production of pinto bean includes farm practices from tillage, fertilizer application, pre-plant herbicide application, planting, rolling, post-emergent herbicide application, inter-row cultivating/scuffing/hilling, fungicide application, pre-harvest desiccation, pull/undercut/knife, windrow/swathing, harvesting, and other field activities, to aeration and drying.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Geographical location of each farm was used to identify the Reconciliation Units (soil and climate based provincial divisions) identified by Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada (AAFC) and AAFC Reporting Zone (ecozone) to which each farm belongs. Production-weighted average datasets were calculated for each ecozone.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Site-specific field data were collected via survey from prairie province pinto bean producers for crop rotation, seeding rate, machinery and fuel use for field operations (e.g., tillage, harrowing, harvest), farm inputs (e.g., fertilizers, pesticides), and electricity for crop drying. Production weighted averages were calculated for the region. Outliers were removed from reported fuel use data based on visual inspection.
